Description: Clapper Corp is a leader in protein co-product equipment service and distribution.
Full Description: Clapper Corporation was established in 1972 by Ted L. Clapper, Jr. as a Mechanical Contractor. Our relationship with The Dupps Company started shortly thereafter as an installer for their rendering systems. In 1978, Ted I. Clapper and Cory L. Kracht became employees of the company. In December 1992, Ted and Cory purchased the company from Ted L. Clapper, Jr., who now acts as company CEO. In 1982 after 200 field installations, Dupps approached Clapper Corporation concerning a distributorship and repair outlet for their equipment. From that point forward, we have been their exclusive Authorized Distributor. We gradually phased out of the mechanical contractor work and concentrated solely on this endeavor. We use only genuine Dupps parts in any of our Dupps equipment repairs. Since 1982, we have overhauled 2000 Dupps pressors and have performed similar repairs to 100 Equacookers. We entered into the prebreaker repair business in 1986 as a supplement to the Dupps equipment repairs. We also build a full line of Rietz and Anco replacement parts. We have overhauled 500 prebreakers since 1986. In 1990, we started rebuilding Svaertek equipment and in 1996, we became the Authorized North American Repair Center for the Danish company Svaertek. Svaertek is a worldwide manufacturer of rendering raw material grinding equipment. During 1991, we began to market centrifuge parts and repair services to the rendering industry as a manufacturer's representative. We currently offer sales, parts, repair and services on both vertical and horizontal centrifuge equipment in a variety of applications. We can design and size equipment to accomodate any and all of your processing needs. We have a vast inventory of equipment available for lease or purchase. Our customer base has grown to include the ethanol industry, soybean, municipalities, and refineries. We work very hard to maintain our good name in the industry and secure a balance between competitive edge and integrity.

Full Description: Grow Utah Ventures, is a privately funded, non-profit organization dedicated to accelerate the creation of innovative, entrepreneur-led, high-growth businesses that will strengthen and expand the future growth of Utah’s economy. The vision of Grow Utah Ventures is to create a robust entrepreneurial eco-system in Utah that fosters entrepreneurial talent, drives innovation to solve market needs, aligns community resources and support, and ensures funding for products, entrepreneurs and businesses of promise. Growing Utah's EntrepreneursGrow Utah Ventures facilitates a wide range of executive leadership initiatives designed to bolster and expand Utah’s entrepreneurial eco-system comprised of talent, ideas, support and funding. We also directly lead entrepreneurial initiatives that promote the creation of new innovations and products addressing a range of market needs. As a result of these initiatives, we increase the likelihood of success of the individual entrepreneurs. We do this with the end objective of building businesses that will aggressively impact the vitality of our economy by creating jobs and increasing individual wealth. Grow Utah Ventures uses its own resources to fill critical gaps needed for economic and entrepreneurial expansion and seek to encourage others to do the same. As such, we serve as a catalyst in forming new partnerships, developing innovative solutions, and capturing emerging opportunities that solve our economic issues today and ensure a sound foundation for our economy in the future.

Description: ZipQ is a complete Self-Checkout Shopper Mobile Application to be used in any Supermarkets reducing long queues.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: ZipQ is a complete Self-Checkout Shopper Mobile Application to be used in any Supermarkets or retail stores where a customer can perform self-checkout service using built-in product scanner and in-app payment gateway system which will help in reducing long queues at physical check-out counters in the supermarket or retail stores.  Using ZipQ shopper could keep a track of his purchased items and eliminate the duplication of work performed at physical Check-Out counters. Stores can benefit by moving their customers at faster rate and reduce installing heavy assets like Check-out counters & POS machines thus could make use of such space for better product visibility. We can save unnecessary paper wastage which goes into Invoice printing by saving e-copies in the handheld device and replication of the same to be saved in shops database.
